00211 \textcolor{comment}{   The SWIG conversion methods, as ConvertPtr, return an integer}
00212 \textcolor{comment}{   that tells if the conversion was successful or not. And if not,}
00213 \textcolor{comment}{   an error code can be returned (see swigerrors.swg for the codes).}
00214 \textcolor{comment}{}
00215 \textcolor{comment}{   Use the following macros/flags to set or process the returning}
00216 \textcolor{comment}{   states.}
00217 \textcolor{comment}{}
00218 \textcolor{comment}{   In old versions of SWIG, code such as the following was usually written:}
00219 \textcolor{comment}{}
00220 \textcolor{comment}{     if (SWIG\_ConvertPtr(obj,vptr,ty.flags) != -1) \{}
00221 \textcolor{comment}{       // success code}
00222 \textcolor{comment}{     \} else \{}
00223 \textcolor{comment}{       //fail code}
00224 \textcolor{comment}{     \}}
00225 \textcolor{comment}{}
00226 \textcolor{comment}{   Now you can be more explicit:}
00227 \textcolor{comment}{}
00228 \textcolor{comment}{    int res = SWIG\_ConvertPtr(obj,vptr,ty.flags);}
00229 \textcolor{comment}{    if (SWIG\_IsOK(res)) \{}
00230 \textcolor{comment}{      // success code}
00231 \textcolor{comment}{    \} else \{}
00232 \textcolor{comment}{      // fail code}
00233 \textcolor{comment}{    \}}
00234 \textcolor{comment}{}
00235 \textcolor{comment}{   which is the same really, but now you can also do}
00236 \textcolor{comment}{}
00237 \textcolor{comment}{    Type *ptr;}
00238 \textcolor{comment}{    int res = SWIG\_ConvertPtr(obj,(void **)(&ptr),ty.flags);}
00239 \textcolor{comment}{    if (SWIG\_IsOK(res)) \{}
00240 \textcolor{comment}{      // success code}
00241 \textcolor{comment}{      if (SWIG\_IsNewObj(res) \{}
00242 \textcolor{comment}{        ...}
00243 \textcolor{comment}{    delete *ptr;}
00244 \textcolor{comment}{      \} else \{}
00245 \textcolor{comment}{        ...}
00246 \textcolor{comment}{      \}}
00247 \textcolor{comment}{    \} else \{}
00248 \textcolor{comment}{      // fail code}
00249 \textcolor{comment}{    \}}
00250 \textcolor{comment}{}
00251 \textcolor{comment}{   I.e., now SWIG\_ConvertPtr can return new objects and you can}
00252 \textcolor{comment}{   identify the case and take care of the deallocation. Of course that}
00253 \textcolor{comment}{   also requires SWIG\_ConvertPtr to return new result values, such as}
00254 \textcolor{comment}{}
00255 \textcolor{comment}{      int SWIG\_ConvertPtr(obj, ptr,...) \{}
00256 \textcolor{comment}{        if (<obj is ok>) \{}
00257 \textcolor{comment}{          if (<need new object>) \{}
00258 \textcolor{comment}{            *ptr = <ptr to new allocated object>;}
00259 \textcolor{comment}{            return SWIG\_NEWOBJ;}
00260 \textcolor{comment}{          \} else \{}
00261 \textcolor{comment}{            *ptr = <ptr to old object>;}
00262 \textcolor{comment}{            return SWIG\_OLDOBJ;}
00263 \textcolor{comment}{          \}}
00264 \textcolor{comment}{        \} else \{}
00265 \textcolor{comment}{          return SWIG\_BADOBJ;}
00266 \textcolor{comment}{        \}}
00267 \textcolor{comment}{      \}}
00268 \textcolor{comment}{}
00269 \textcolor{comment}{   Of course, returning the plain '0(success)/-1(fail)' still works, but you can be}
00270 \textcolor{comment}{   more explicit by returning SWIG\_BADOBJ, SWIG\_ERROR or any of the}
00271 \textcolor{comment}{   SWIG errors code.}

00277 \textcolor{comment}{       int fooi(int);}
00278 \textcolor{comment}{}
00279 \textcolor{comment}{   and you call}
00280 \textcolor{comment}{}
00281 \textcolor{comment}{      food(1)   // cast rank '1'  (1 -> 1.0)}
00282 \textcolor{comment}{      fooi(1)   // cast rank '0'}
00283 \textcolor{comment}{}
00284 \textcolor{comment}{   just use the SWIG\_AddCast()/SWIG\_CheckState()}
00285 \textcolor{comment}{*/}

00382   \textcolor{keywordflow}{for} (;(f1 != l1) && (f2 != l2); ++f1, ++f2) \{
00383     \textcolor{keywordflow}{while} ((*f1 == \textcolor{charliteral}{' '}) && (f1 != l1)) ++f1;
00384     \textcolor{keywordflow}{while} ((*f2 == \textcolor{charliteral}{' '}) && (f2 != l2)) ++f2;
00385     \textcolor{keywordflow}{if} (*f1 != *f2) \textcolor{keywordflow}{return} (*f1 > *f2) ? 1 : -1;
00386   \}
00387   \textcolor{keywordflow}{return} (\textcolor{keywordtype}{int})((l1 - f1) - (l2 - f2));
00388 \}

00390 \textcolor{comment}{/*}
00391 \textcolor{comment}{  Check type equivalence in a name list like <name1>|<name2>|...}
00392 \textcolor{comment}{  Return 0 if equal, -1 if nb < tb, 1 if nb > tb}
00393 \textcolor{comment}{*/}
00394 SWIGRUNTIME \textcolor{keywordtype}{int}
00395 SWIG_TypeCmp(\textcolor{keyword}{const} \textcolor{keywordtype}{char} *nb, \textcolor{keyword}{const} \textcolor{keywordtype}{char} *tb) \{
00396   \textcolor{keywordtype}{int} equiv = 1;
00397   \textcolor{keyword}{const} \textcolor{keywordtype}{char}* te = tb + strlen(tb);
00398   \textcolor{keyword}{const} \textcolor{keywordtype}{char}* ne = nb;
00399   \textcolor{keywordflow}{while} (equiv != 0 && *ne) \{
00400     \textcolor{keywordflow}{for} (nb = ne; *ne; ++ne) \{
00401       \textcolor{keywordflow}{if} (*ne == \textcolor{charliteral}{'|'}) \textcolor{keywordflow}{break};
00402     \}
00403     equiv = SWIG_TypeNameComp(nb, ne, tb, te);
00404     \textcolor{keywordflow}{if} (*ne) ++ne;
00405   \}
00406   \textcolor{keywordflow}{return} equiv;
00407 \}
00408 
00409 \textcolor{comment}{/*}
00410 \textcolor{comment}{  Check type equivalence in a name list like <name1>|<name2>|...}
00411 \textcolor{comment}{  Return 0 if not equal, 1 if equal}
00412 \textcolor{comment}{*/}
00413 SWIGRUNTIME \textcolor{keywordtype}{int}
00414 SWIG_TypeEquiv(\textcolor{keyword}{const} \textcolor{keywordtype}{char} *nb, \textcolor{keyword}{const} \textcolor{keywordtype}{char} *tb) \{
00415   \textcolor{keywordflow}{return} SWIG_TypeCmp(nb, tb) == 0 ? 1 : 0;
00416 \}

00418 \textcolor{comment}{/*}
00419 \textcolor{comment}{  Check the typename}
00420 \textcolor{comment}{*/}
00421 SWIGRUNTIME swig_cast_info *
00422 SWIG_TypeCheck(\textcolor{keyword}{const} \textcolor{keywordtype}{char} *c, swig_type_info *ty) \{
00423   \textcolor{keywordflow}{if} (ty) \{
00424     swig_cast_info *iter = ty->cast;
00425     \textcolor{keywordflow}{while} (iter) \{
00426       \textcolor{keywordflow}{if} (strcmp(iter->type->name, c) == 0) \{
00427         \textcolor{keywordflow}{if} (iter == ty->cast)
00428           \textcolor{keywordflow}{return} iter;
00429         \textcolor{comment}{/* Move iter to the top of the linked list */}
00430         iter->prev->next = iter->next;
00431         \textcolor{keywordflow}{if} (iter->next)
00432           iter->next->prev = iter->prev;
00433         iter->next = ty->cast;
00434         iter->prev = 0;
00435         \textcolor{keywordflow}{if} (ty->cast) ty->cast->prev = iter;
00436         ty->cast = iter;
00437         \textcolor{keywordflow}{return} iter;
00438       \}
00439       iter = iter->next;
00440     \}
00441   \}
00442   \textcolor{keywordflow}{return} 0;
00443 \}

00445 \textcolor{comment}{/*}
00446 \textcolor{comment}{  Identical to SWIG\_TypeCheck, except strcmp is replaced with a pointer comparison}
00447 \textcolor{comment}{*/}
00448 SWIGRUNTIME swig_cast_info *
00449 SWIG_TypeCheckStruct(swig_type_info *from, swig_type_info *ty) \{
00450   \textcolor{keywordflow}{if} (ty) \{
00451     swig_cast_info *iter = ty->cast;
00452     \textcolor{keywordflow}{while} (iter) \{
00453       \textcolor{keywordflow}{if} (iter->type == from) \{
00454         \textcolor{keywordflow}{if} (iter == ty->cast)
00455           \textcolor{keywordflow}{return} iter;
00456         \textcolor{comment}{/* Move iter to the top of the linked list */}
00457         iter->prev->next = iter->next;
00458         \textcolor{keywordflow}{if} (iter->next)
00459           iter->next->prev = iter->prev;
00460         iter->next = ty->cast;
00461         iter->prev = 0;
00462         \textcolor{keywordflow}{if} (ty->cast) ty->cast->prev = iter;
00463         ty->cast = iter;
00464         \textcolor{keywordflow}{return} iter;
00465       \}
00466       iter = iter->next;
00467     \}
00468   \}
00469   \textcolor{keywordflow}{return} 0;
00470 \}

00472 \textcolor{comment}{/*}
00473 \textcolor{comment}{  Cast a pointer up an inheritance hierarchy}
00474 \textcolor{comment}{*/}
00475 SWIGRUNTIMEINLINE \textcolor{keywordtype}{void} *
00476 SWIG_TypeCast(swig_cast_info *ty, \textcolor{keywordtype}{void} *ptr, \textcolor{keywordtype}{int} *newmemory) \{
00477   \textcolor{keywordflow}{return} ((!ty) || (!ty->converter)) ? ptr : (*ty->converter)(ptr, newmemory);
00478 \}

00480 \textcolor{comment}{/*}
00481 \textcolor{comment}{   Dynamic pointer casting. Down an inheritance hierarchy}
00482 \textcolor{comment}{*/}
00483 SWIGRUNTIME swig_type_info *
00484 SWIG_TypeDynamicCast(swig_type_info *ty, \textcolor{keywordtype}{void} **ptr) \{
00485   swig_type_info *lastty = ty;
00486   \textcolor{keywordflow}{if} (!ty || !ty->dcast) \textcolor{keywordflow}{return} ty;
00487   \textcolor{keywordflow}{while} (ty && (ty->dcast)) \{
00488     ty = (*ty->dcast)(ptr);
00489     \textcolor{keywordflow}{if} (ty) lastty = ty;
00490   \}
00491   \textcolor{keywordflow}{return} lastty;
00492 \}

00494 \textcolor{comment}{/*}
00495 \textcolor{comment}{  Return the name associated with this type}

00497 SWIGRUNTIMEINLINE \textcolor{keyword}{const} \textcolor{keywordtype}{char} *
00498 SWIG_TypeName(\textcolor{keyword}{const} swig_type_info *ty) \{

00502 \textcolor{comment}{/*}
00503 \textcolor{comment}{  Return the pretty name associated with this type,}
00504 \textcolor{comment}{  that is an unmangled type name in a form presentable to the user.}
00505 \textcolor{comment}{*/}
00506 SWIGRUNTIME \textcolor{keyword}{const} \textcolor{keywordtype}{char} *
00507 SWIG_TypePrettyName(\textcolor{keyword}{const} swig_type_info *type) \{
00508   \textcolor{comment}{/* The "str" field contains the equivalent pretty names of the}
00509 \textcolor{comment}{     type, separated by vertical-bar characters.  We choose}
00510 \textcolor{comment}{     to print the last name, as it is often (?) the most}
00511 \textcolor{comment}{     specific. */}
00512   \textcolor{keywordflow}{if} (!type) \textcolor{keywordflow}{return} NULL;
00513   \textcolor{keywordflow}{if} (type->str != NULL) \{
00514     \textcolor{keyword}{const} \textcolor{keywordtype}{char} *last\_name = type->str;
00515     \textcolor{keyword}{const} \textcolor{keywordtype}{char} *s;
00516     \textcolor{keywordflow}{for} (s = type->str; *s; s++)
00517       \textcolor{keywordflow}{if} (*s == \textcolor{charliteral}{'|'}) last\_name = s+1;
00518     \textcolor{keywordflow}{return} last\_name;
00519   \}
00520   \textcolor{keywordflow}{else}
00521     \textcolor{keywordflow}{return} type->name;
00522 \}

00524 \textcolor{comment}{/*}

00526 \textcolor{comment}{*/}
00527 SWIGRUNTIME \textcolor{keywordtype}{void}
00528 SWIG_TypeClientData(swig_type_info *ti, \textcolor{keywordtype}{void} *clientdata) \{
00529   swig_cast_info *cast = ti->cast;
00530   \textcolor{comment}{/* if (ti->clientdata == clientdata) return; */}

00535       swig_type_info *tc = cast->type;
00536       \textcolor{keywordflow}{if} (!tc->clientdata) \{
00537     SWIG_TypeClientData(tc, clientdata);
00538       \}
00539     \}

00544 SWIG_TypeNewClientData(swig_type_info *ti, \textcolor{keywordtype}{void} *clientdata) \{

00549 \textcolor{comment}{/*}
00550 \textcolor{comment}{  Search for a swig\_type\_info structure only by mangled name}
00551 \textcolor{comment}{  Search is a O(log #types)}
00552 \textcolor{comment}{}
00553 \textcolor{comment}{  We start searching at module start, and finish searching when start == end.}
00554 \textcolor{comment}{  Note: if start == end at the beginning of the function, we go all the way around}
00555 \textcolor{comment}{  the circular list.}
00556 \textcolor{comment}{*/}
00557 SWIGRUNTIME swig_type_info *
00558 SWIG_MangledTypeQueryModule(swig_module_info *start,
00559                             swig_module_info *end,
00560                     \textcolor{keyword}{const} \textcolor{keywordtype}{char} *name) \{
00561   swig_module_info *iter = start;
00562   \textcolor{keywordflow}{do} \{
00563     \textcolor{keywordflow}{if} (iter->size) \{
00564       \textcolor{keyword}{register} \textcolor{keywordtype}{size\_t} l = 0;
00565       \textcolor{keyword}{register} \textcolor{keywordtype}{size\_t} r = iter->size - 1;
00566       \textcolor{keywordflow}{do} \{
00567     \textcolor{comment}{/* since l+r >= 0, we can (>> 1) instead (/ 2) */}
00568     \textcolor{keyword}{register} \textcolor{keywordtype}{size\_t} i = (l + r) >> 1;
00569     \textcolor{keyword}{const} \textcolor{keywordtype}{char} *iname = iter->types[i]->name;
00570     \textcolor{keywordflow}{if} (iname) \{
00571       \textcolor{keyword}{register} \textcolor{keywordtype}{int} compare = strcmp(name, iname);
00572       \textcolor{keywordflow}{if} (compare == 0) \{
00573         \textcolor{keywordflow}{return} iter->types[i];
00574       \} \textcolor{keywordflow}{else} \textcolor{keywordflow}{if} (compare < 0) \{
00575         \textcolor{keywordflow}{if} (i) \{
00576           r = i - 1;
00577         \} \textcolor{keywordflow}{else} \{
00578           \textcolor{keywordflow}{break};
00579         \}
00580       \} \textcolor{keywordflow}{else} \textcolor{keywordflow}{if} (compare > 0) \{
00581         l = i + 1;
00582       \}
00583     \} \textcolor{keywordflow}{else} \{
00584       \textcolor{keywordflow}{break}; \textcolor{comment}{/* should never happen */}
00585     \}
00586       \} \textcolor{keywordflow}{while} (l <= r);
00587     \}
00588     iter = iter->next;
00589   \} \textcolor{keywordflow}{while} (iter != end);
00590   \textcolor{keywordflow}{return} 0;
00591 \}
00592 
00593 \textcolor{comment}{/*}
00594 \textcolor{comment}{  Search for a swig\_type\_info structure for either a mangled name or a human readable name.}
00595 \textcolor{comment}{  It first searches the mangled names of the types, which is a O(log #types)}
00596 \textcolor{comment}{  If a type is not found it then searches the human readable names, which is O(#types).}
00597 \textcolor{comment}{}
00598 \textcolor{comment}{  We start searching at module start, and finish searching when start == end.}
00599 \textcolor{comment}{  Note: if start == end at the beginning of the function, we go all the way around}
00600 \textcolor{comment}{  the circular list.}
00601 \textcolor{comment}{*/}
00602 SWIGRUNTIME swig_type_info *
00603 SWIG_TypeQueryModule(swig_module_info *start,
00604                      swig_module_info *end,
00605              \textcolor{keyword}{const} \textcolor{keywordtype}{char} *name) \{
00606   \textcolor{comment}{/* STEP 1: Search the name field using binary search */}
00607   swig_type_info *ret = SWIG_MangledTypeQueryModule(start, end, name);
00608   \textcolor{keywordflow}{if} (ret) \{
00609     \textcolor{keywordflow}{return} ret;
00610   \} \textcolor{keywordflow}{else} \{
00611     \textcolor{comment}{/* STEP 2: If the type hasn't been found, do a complete search}
00612 \textcolor{comment}{       of the str field (the human readable name) */}
00613     swig_module_info *iter = start;
00614     \textcolor{keywordflow}{do} \{
00615       \textcolor{keyword}{register} \textcolor{keywordtype}{size\_t} i = 0;
00616       \textcolor{keywordflow}{for} (; i < iter->size; ++i) \{
00617     \textcolor{keywordflow}{if} (iter->types[i]->str && (SWIG_TypeEquiv(iter->types[i]->str, name)))
00618       \textcolor{keywordflow}{return} iter->types[i];
00619       \}
00620       iter = iter->next;
00621     \} \textcolor{keywordflow}{while} (iter != end);
00622   \}
00623 
00624   \textcolor{comment}{/* neither found a match */}
00625   \textcolor{keywordflow}{return} 0;
00626 \}
00627 
00628 \textcolor{comment}{/*}
00629 \textcolor{comment}{   Pack binary data into a string}
00630 \textcolor{comment}{*/}
00631 SWIGRUNTIME \textcolor{keywordtype}{char} *
00632 SWIG_PackData(\textcolor{keywordtype}{char} *c, \textcolor{keywordtype}{void} *ptr, \textcolor{keywordtype}{size\_t} sz) \{
00633   \textcolor{keyword}{static} \textcolor{keyword}{const} \textcolor{keywordtype}{char} hex[17] = \textcolor{stringliteral}{"0123456789abcdef"};
00634   \textcolor{keyword}{register} \textcolor{keyword}{const} \textcolor{keywordtype}{unsigned} \textcolor{keywordtype}{char} *u = (\textcolor{keywordtype}{unsigned} \textcolor{keywordtype}{char} *) ptr;
00635   \textcolor{keyword}{register} \textcolor{keyword}{const} \textcolor{keywordtype}{unsigned} \textcolor{keywordtype}{char} *eu =  u + sz;
00636   \textcolor{keywordflow}{for} (; u != eu; ++u) \{
00637     \textcolor{keyword}{register} \textcolor{keywordtype}{unsigned} \textcolor{keywordtype}{char} uu = *u;
00638     *(c++) = hex[(uu & 0xf0) >> 4];
00639     *(c++) = hex[uu & 0xf];
00640   \}
00641   \textcolor{keywordflow}{return} c;
00642 \}
00643 
00644 \textcolor{comment}{/*}
00645 \textcolor{comment}{   Unpack binary data from a string}
00646 \textcolor{comment}{*/}
00647 SWIGRUNTIME \textcolor{keyword}{const} \textcolor{keywordtype}{char} *
00648 SWIG_UnpackData(\textcolor{keyword}{const} \textcolor{keywordtype}{char} *c, \textcolor{keywordtype}{void} *ptr, \textcolor{keywordtype}{size\_t} sz) \{
00649   \textcolor{keyword}{register} \textcolor{keywordtype}{unsigned} \textcolor{keywordtype}{char} *u = (\textcolor{keywordtype}{unsigned} \textcolor{keywordtype}{char} *) ptr;
00650   \textcolor{keyword}{register} \textcolor{keyword}{const} \textcolor{keywordtype}{unsigned} \textcolor{keywordtype}{char} *eu = u + sz;
00651   \textcolor{keywordflow}{for} (; u != eu; ++u) \{
00652     \textcolor{keyword}{register} \textcolor{keywordtype}{char} d = *(c++);
00653     \textcolor{keyword}{register} \textcolor{keywordtype}{unsigned} \textcolor{keywordtype}{char} uu;
00654     \textcolor{keywordflow}{if} ((d >= \textcolor{charliteral}{'0'}) && (d <= \textcolor{charliteral}{'9'}))
00655       uu = ((d - \textcolor{charliteral}{'0'}) << 4);
00656     \textcolor{keywordflow}{else} \textcolor{keywordflow}{if} ((d >= \textcolor{charliteral}{'a'}) && (d <= \textcolor{charliteral}{'f'}))
00657       uu = ((d - (\textcolor{charliteral}{'a'}-10)) << 4);
00658     \textcolor{keywordflow}{else}
00659       \textcolor{keywordflow}{return} (\textcolor{keywordtype}{char} *) 0;
00660     d = *(c++);
00661     \textcolor{keywordflow}{if} ((d >= \textcolor{charliteral}{'0'}) && (d <= \textcolor{charliteral}{'9'}))
00662       uu |= (d - \textcolor{charliteral}{'0'});
00663     \textcolor{keywordflow}{else} \textcolor{keywordflow}{if} ((d >= \textcolor{charliteral}{'a'}) && (d <= \textcolor{charliteral}{'f'}))
00664       uu |= (d - (\textcolor{charliteral}{'a'}-10));
00665     \textcolor{keywordflow}{else}
00666       \textcolor{keywordflow}{return} (\textcolor{keywordtype}{char} *) 0;
00667     *u = uu;
00668   \}
00669   \textcolor{keywordflow}{return} c;
00670 \}
00671 
00672 \textcolor{comment}{/*}
00673 \textcolor{comment}{   Pack 'void *' into a string buffer.}
00674 \textcolor{comment}{*/}
00675 SWIGRUNTIME \textcolor{keywordtype}{char} *
00676 SWIG_PackVoidPtr(\textcolor{keywordtype}{char} *buff, \textcolor{keywordtype}{void} *ptr, \textcolor{keyword}{const} \textcolor{keywordtype}{char} *name, \textcolor{keywordtype}{size\_t} bsz) \{
00677   \textcolor{keywordtype}{char} *r = buff;
00678   \textcolor{keywordflow}{if} ((2*\textcolor{keyword}{sizeof}(\textcolor{keywordtype}{void} *) + 2) > bsz) \textcolor{keywordflow}{return} 0;
00679   *(r++) = \textcolor{charliteral}{'\_'};
00680   r = SWIG_PackData(r,&ptr,\textcolor{keyword}{sizeof}(\textcolor{keywordtype}{void} *));
00681   \textcolor{keywordflow}{if} (strlen(name) + 1 > (bsz - (r - buff))) \textcolor{keywordflow}{return} 0;
00682   strcpy(r,name);
00683   \textcolor{keywordflow}{return} buff;
00684 \}
00685 
00686 SWIGRUNTIME \textcolor{keyword}{const} \textcolor{keywordtype}{char} *
00687 SWIG_UnpackVoidPtr(\textcolor{keyword}{const} \textcolor{keywordtype}{char} *c, \textcolor{keywordtype}{void} **ptr, \textcolor{keyword}{const} \textcolor{keywordtype}{char} *name) \{
00688   \textcolor{keywordflow}{if} (*c != \textcolor{charliteral}{'\_'}) \{
00689     \textcolor{keywordflow}{if} (strcmp(c,\textcolor{stringliteral}{"NULL"}) == 0) \{
00690       *ptr = (\textcolor{keywordtype}{void} *) 0;
00691       \textcolor{keywordflow}{return} name;
00692     \} \textcolor{keywordflow}{else} \{
00693       \textcolor{keywordflow}{return} 0;
00694     \}
00695   \}
00696   \textcolor{keywordflow}{return} SWIG_UnpackData(++c,ptr,\textcolor{keyword}{sizeof}(\textcolor{keywordtype}{void} *));
00697 \}
00698 
00699 SWIGRUNTIME \textcolor{keywordtype}{char} *
00700 SWIG_PackDataName(\textcolor{keywordtype}{char} *buff, \textcolor{keywordtype}{void} *ptr, \textcolor{keywordtype}{size\_t} sz, \textcolor{keyword}{const} \textcolor{keywordtype}{char} *name, \textcolor{keywordtype}{size\_t} bsz) \{
00701   \textcolor{keywordtype}{char} *r = buff;
00702   \textcolor{keywordtype}{size\_t} lname = (name ? strlen(name) : 0);
00703   \textcolor{keywordflow}{if} ((2*sz + 2 + lname) > bsz) \textcolor{keywordflow}{return} 0;
00704   *(r++) = \textcolor{charliteral}{'\_'};
00705   r = SWIG_PackData(r,ptr,sz);
00706   \textcolor{keywordflow}{if} (lname) \{
00707     strncpy(r,name,lname+1);
00708   \} \textcolor{keywordflow}{else} \{
00709     *r = 0;
00710   \}
00711   \textcolor{keywordflow}{return} buff;
00712 \}
00713 
00714 SWIGRUNTIME \textcolor{keyword}{const} \textcolor{keywordtype}{char} *
00715 SWIG_UnpackDataName(\textcolor{keyword}{const} \textcolor{keywordtype}{char} *c, \textcolor{keywordtype}{void} *ptr, \textcolor{keywordtype}{size\_t} sz, \textcolor{keyword}{const} \textcolor{keywordtype}{char} *name) \{
00716   \textcolor{keywordflow}{if} (*c != \textcolor{charliteral}{'\_'}) \{
00717     \textcolor{keywordflow}{if} (strcmp(c,\textcolor{stringliteral}{"NULL"}) == 0) \{
00718       memset(ptr,0,sz);
00719       \textcolor{keywordflow}{return} name;
00720     \} \textcolor{keywordflow}{else} \{
00721       \textcolor{keywordflow}{return} 0;
00722     \}
00723   \}
00724   \textcolor{keywordflow}{return} SWIG_UnpackData(++c,ptr,sz);
00725 \}

00781 \textcolor{comment}{/* Warning: This function will allocate a new string in Python 3,}

00784 SWIGINTERN \textcolor{keywordtype}{char}*
00785 SWIG_Python_str_AsChar(PyObject *str)
00786 \{
00787 \textcolor{preprocessor}{#if PY\_VERSION\_HEX >= 0x03000000}
00788   \textcolor{keywordtype}{char} *cstr;
00789   \textcolor{keywordtype}{char} *newstr;

01316 SWIGINTERN \textcolor{keywordtype}{int}

01320     \textcolor{keywordflow}{if} (!min && !max) \{
01321       \textcolor{keywordflow}{return} 1;
01322     \} \textcolor{keywordflow}{else} \{
01323       PyErr\_Format(PyExc\_TypeError, \textcolor{stringliteral}{"%s expected %s%d arguments, got none"}, 
01324            name, (min == max ? \textcolor{stringliteral}{""} : \textcolor{stringliteral}{"at least "}), (\textcolor{keywordtype}{int})min);
01325       \textcolor{keywordflow}{return} 0;
01326     \}
01327   \}  
01328   \textcolor{keywordflow}{if} (!PyTuple\_Check(args)) \{
01329     \textcolor{keywordflow}{if} (min <= 1 && max >= 1) \{
01330       \textcolor{keyword}{register} \textcolor{keywordtype}{int} i;
01331       objs[0] = args;
01332       \textcolor{keywordflow}{for} (i = 1; i < max; ++i) \{
01333     objs[i] = 0;
01334       \}
01335       \textcolor{keywordflow}{return} 2;
01336     \}

01338     \textcolor{keywordflow}{return} 0;

01341     \textcolor{keywordflow}{if} (l < min) \{
01342       PyErr\_Format(PyExc\_TypeError, \textcolor{stringliteral}{"%s expected %s%d arguments, got %d"}, 
01343            name, (min == max ? \textcolor{stringliteral}{""} : \textcolor{stringliteral}{"at least "}), (\textcolor{keywordtype}{int})min, (\textcolor{keywordtype}{int})l);
01344       \textcolor{keywordflow}{return} 0;
01345     \} \textcolor{keywordflow}{else} \textcolor{keywordflow}{if} (l > max) \{
01346       PyErr\_Format(PyExc\_TypeError, \textcolor{stringliteral}{"%s expected %s%d arguments, got %d"}, 
01347            name, (min == max ? \textcolor{stringliteral}{""} : \textcolor{stringliteral}{"at most "}), (\textcolor{keywordtype}{int})max, (\textcolor{keywordtype}{int})l);
01348       \textcolor{keywordflow}{return} 0;
01349     \} \textcolor{keywordflow}{else} \{
01350       \textcolor{keyword}{register} \textcolor{keywordtype}{int} i;
01351       \textcolor{keywordflow}{for} (i = 0; i < l; ++i) \{
01352     objs[i] = PyTuple\_GET\_ITEM(args, i);
01353       \}

01355     objs[l] = 0;
01356       \}

01358     \}

03303    \textcolor{keywordtype}{double} fx = floor(x);
03304    \textcolor{keywordtype}{double} cx = ceil(x);
03305    \textcolor{keywordtype}{double} rd =  ((x - fx) < 0.5) ? fx : cx; \textcolor{comment}{/* simple rint */}

03307      errno = 0;
03308    \} \textcolor{keywordflow}{else} \{
03309      \textcolor{keywordtype}{double} summ, reps, diff;
03310      \textcolor{keywordflow}{if} (rd < x) \{

03313        diff = rd - x;
03314      \} \textcolor{keywordflow}{else} \{
03315        \textcolor{keywordflow}{return} 1;
03316      \}
03317      summ = rd + x;
03318      reps = diff/summ;
03319      \textcolor{keywordflow}{if} (reps < 8*DBL\_EPSILON) \{

03321        \textcolor{keywordflow}{return} 1;
03322      \}

41227 \textcolor{comment}{/* -----------------------------------------------------------------------------}
41228 \textcolor{comment}{ * Type initialization:}
41229 \textcolor{comment}{ * This problem is tough by the requirement that no dynamic}
41230 \textcolor{comment}{ * memory is used. Also, since swig\_type\_info structures store pointers to}
41231 \textcolor{comment}{ * swig\_cast\_info structures and swig\_cast\_info structures store pointers back}
41232 \textcolor{comment}{ * to swig\_type\_info structures, we need some lookup code at initialization.}
41233 \textcolor{comment}{ * The idea is that swig generates all the structures that are needed.}
41234 \textcolor{comment}{ * The runtime then collects these partially filled structures.}
41235 \textcolor{comment}{ * The SWIG\_InitializeModule function takes these initial arrays out of}
41236 \textcolor{comment}{ * swig\_module, and does all the lookup, filling in the swig\_module.types}
41237 \textcolor{comment}{ * array with the correct data and linking the correct swig\_cast\_info}
41238 \textcolor{comment}{ * structures together.}
41239 \textcolor{comment}{ *}
41240 \textcolor{comment}{ * The generated swig\_type\_info structures are assigned staticly to an initial}
41241 \textcolor{comment}{ * array. We just loop through that array, and handle each type individually.}
41242 \textcolor{comment}{ * First we lookup if this type has been already loaded, and if so, use the}
41243 \textcolor{comment}{ * loaded structure instead of the generated one. Then we have to fill in the}
41244 \textcolor{comment}{ * cast linked list. The cast data is initially stored in something like a}
41245 \textcolor{comment}{ * two-dimensional array. Each row corresponds to a type (there are the same}
41246 \textcolor{comment}{ * number of rows as there are in the swig\_type\_initial array). Each entry in}
41247 \textcolor{comment}{ * a column is one of the swig\_cast\_info structures for that type.}
41248 \textcolor{comment}{ * The cast\_initial array is actually an array of arrays, because each row has}
41249 \textcolor{comment}{ * a variable number of columns. So to actually build the cast linked list,}
41250 \textcolor{comment}{ * we find the array of casts associated with the type, and loop through it}
41251 \textcolor{comment}{ * adding the casts to the list. The one last trick we need to do is making}
41252 \textcolor{comment}{ * sure the type pointer in the swig\_cast\_info struct is correct.}
41253 \textcolor{comment}{ *}
41254 \textcolor{comment}{ * First off, we lookup the cast->type name to see if it is already loaded.}
41255 \textcolor{comment}{ * There are three cases to handle:}
41256 \textcolor{comment}{ *  1) If the cast->type has already been loaded AND the type we are adding}
41257 \textcolor{comment}{ *     casting info to has not been loaded (it is in this module), THEN we}
41258 \textcolor{comment}{ *     replace the cast->type pointer with the type pointer that has already}
41259 \textcolor{comment}{ *     been loaded.}
41260 \textcolor{comment}{ *  2) If BOTH types (the one we are adding casting info to, and the}
41261 \textcolor{comment}{ *     cast->type) are loaded, THEN the cast info has already been loaded by}
41262 \textcolor{comment}{ *     the previous module so we just ignore it.}
41263 \textcolor{comment}{ *  3) Finally, if cast->type has not already been loaded, then we add that}
41264 \textcolor{comment}{ *     swig\_cast\_info to the linked list (because the cast->type) pointer will}
41265 \textcolor{comment}{ *     be correct.}
41266 \textcolor{comment}{ * ----------------------------------------------------------------------------- */}

41281 SWIG_InitializeModule(\textcolor{keywordtype}{void} *clientdata) \{
41282   \textcolor{keywordtype}{size\_t} i;
41283   swig_module_info *module\_head, *iter;
41284   \textcolor{keywordtype}{int} found, init;
41285   
41286   \textcolor{comment}{/* check to see if the circular list has been setup, if not, set it up */}
41287   \textcolor{keywordflow}{if} (swig\_module.next==0) \{
41288     \textcolor{comment}{/* Initialize the swig\_module */}
41289     swig\_module.type_initial = swig_type_initial;
41290     swig\_module.cast_initial = swig_cast_initial;
41291     swig\_module.next = &swig_module;
41292     init = 1;
41293   \} \textcolor{keywordflow}{else} \{
41294     init = 0;
41295   \}
41296   
41297   \textcolor{comment}{/* Try and load any already created modules */}
41298   module\_head = SWIG_GetModule(clientdata);
41299   \textcolor{keywordflow}{if} (!module\_head) \{
41300     \textcolor{comment}{/* This is the first module loaded for this interpreter */}
41301     \textcolor{comment}{/* so set the swig module into the interpreter */}
41302     SWIG_SetModule(clientdata, &swig\_module);
41303     module\_head = &swig_module;
41304   \} \textcolor{keywordflow}{else} \{
41305     \textcolor{comment}{/* the interpreter has loaded a SWIG module, but has it loaded this one? */}
41306     found=0;
41307     iter=module\_head;
41308     \textcolor{keywordflow}{do} \{
41309       \textcolor{keywordflow}{if} (iter==&swig\_module) \{
41310         found=1;
41311         \textcolor{keywordflow}{break};
41312       \}
41313       iter=iter->next;
41314     \} \textcolor{keywordflow}{while} (iter!= module\_head);
41315     
41316     \textcolor{comment}{/* if the is found in the list, then all is done and we may leave */}
41317     \textcolor{keywordflow}{if} (found) \textcolor{keywordflow}{return};
